Make surprise attacks! Try building on all the corners of the map in addition to the center. Most people never suspect an attack from behind or a base in one of the corners. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/5/55/Be-Good-at-Death-Match-in-Age-of-Mythology-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Be-Good-at-Death-Match-in-Age-of-Mythology-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"/images/thumb/5/55/Be-Good-at-Death-Match-in-Age-of-Mythology-Step-4Bullet2.jpg/aid465408-v4-728px-Be-Good-at-Death-Match-in-Age-of-Mythology-Step-4Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":"728","bigHeight":"546","licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
